☠ MORTAL KEYS — The Keyboard Slayer
Retro arcade-style piano keyboard trainer inspired by Mortal Kombat. 8 game modes across Identification and Construction. Sister game to Mortal Frets.
🎮 Play Now

Game Modes
All modes: 10 questions per round · Score = errors (fewer = better) · Tiebreaker: time · Default notation: Do-Re-Mi
Identification — see the question on the keyboard, press the correct button
ModeWhat you seeFeedbackNote IDKey highlighted, always Do4–Si4 (central octave)Wrong button plays that noteInterval IDR (root, green) + interval key (orange)Wrong button plays that intervalChord IDClose voicing, all inversionsWrong button plays root-position arpeggio · Correct: chord name + inversion shown 2sScale IDScale in octave box, R = Root (red), outside darkenedWrong button plays that scale · Correct: root + scale name shown 2s
Construction — target illuminated, click keys, press SUBMIT
ModePre-placedWhat you doNote Construction—Place both occurrences (one per octave)Interval ConstructionR (green)Click nearest note above — auto-checksChord ConstructionOne tone (amber, role label)Click remaining tones, no duplicatesScale ConstructionR (red) in octave boxFill all scale notes

Rules

Variety: same type appears at most twice per round; exact same question never repeats
Mercy ☠: activates after 2 wrong answers — hold to reveal solution on keyboard; correct answer button lights gold. Release to retry.
Octave box: Chord and Scale modes — fixed octave range (Do–Do, Re–Re…) or 💀 KHAOS (random each question)
Active Chords / Scales: deselect types in the lobby to skip them; show ✕ in-game
Leaderboard: ALL or SAME CONFIG
Notation: toggle A-B-C / Do-Re-Mi (default: Do-Re-Mi)


Scoring
ErrorsResult0⚡ FLAWLESS VICTORY1–2EXCELLENT3–5SKILLED6–10FIGHT HARDER11–19FINISH HIM20+FATALITY

Music Theory Coverage
Notes: all 12 chromatic, central octave Do4–Si4 (MIDI 60–71)
Intervals: m2 · M2 · m3 · M3 · P4 · TT · P5 · m6 · M6 · m7 · M7 · P8
Chords: Maj · min · Aug · Dim · Maj7 · Dom7 · min7 · ø7 · °7
Scales: Major · Natural Minor · Harmonic Minor · Melodic Minor · Whole-Half Dim · Half-Whole Dim
Voicings: close voicing, all inversions, bass note in selected octave box

Deploy

Upload mortal_keys.html renamed as index.html
GitHub Settings → Pages → branch main → / (root)


Firebase Setup
Uses same Firebase project as Mortal Frets, path mortalkeys/.
Add to Realtime Database Rules:
json{
  "rules": {
    "leaderboards": {
      "$mode": { ".read": true, ".write": true }
    },
    "mortalkeys": {
      "leaderboards": {
        "$mode": { ".read": true, ".write": true }
      }
    }
  }
}
Replace FB_CONFIG in <script> with your project values (same as Mortal Frets).

Tech
Pure HTML/CSS/JS · Web Audio API · SVG keyboard (2 octaves) · Firebase REST API · Press Start 2P + Rajdhani · CRT scanlines · iOS silent switch bypass
